{% comment %}theme-check-disable ImgLazyLoading{% endcomment %}
{% comment %}
  Renders a product image with a modal-opener

  Accepts:
  - media: {Object} Product Media object
  - position: {String} Position of the media. Used for accessible label.
  - loop: {Boolean} Enable video looping (optional)
  - modal_id: {String} The product modal that will be shown by clicking the image
  - xr_button: {Boolean} Renders the "View in your space" button (shopify-xr-button) if the media is a 3D Model
  - media_width: {Float} The width percentage that the media column occupies on desktop.
  - image_ratio: {String} The setting either show the article image ratio
  - mobile_image_ratio: {String} The setting either show the article image ratio on mobile
  - lazy_load: {Boolean} Image should be lazy loaded. Default: true (optional)

  Usage:
  {% render 'product-image',
    media: media,
    position: forloop.index,
    zoom: section.settings.enable_image_zoom,
    loop: section.settings.enable_video_looping,
    modal_id: section.id
  %}
{% endcomment %}

{%- comment -%}
  CWV FIX (LCP): `sizes` deve refletir exatamente o `imagesizes` do
  <link rel="preload" as="image"> emitido em layout/theme.liquid para
  request.page_type == 'product'. Qualquer divergência faz o preloader
  escolher uma URL do srcset e o <img> pedir outra, forçando re-download.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture sizes -%}(min-width: 990px) calc({{ media_width | times: 100 }}vw - 10rem), (min-width: 750px) calc((100vw - 10rem) / 2), calc(100vw - 3rem){%- endcapture -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    Default to lazy-loading to keep mobile swiping smooth.
    Only load eagerly when `lazy_load: false` is explicitly passed.
  endcomment
  assign image_loading = 'lazy'
  if lazy_load == false
    assign image_loading = 'eager'
  endif

  assign image_decoding = 'async'
  assign image_fetchpriority = 'auto'
  if position == 'featured' and image_loading == 'eager'
    assign image_fetchpriority = 'high'
  endif

  assign alt = media.alt | escape | split: '#' | first

  assign widths = '165, 360, 535, 750, 900, 1200'

  assign is_lcp_image = false
  if position == 'featured' and image_loading == 'eager' and media.media_type == 'image'
    assign is_lcp_image = true
  endif

  assign preview_aspect = media.preview_image.aspect_ratio | default: 1
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================================
  CWV FIX (CLS 0.494 → 0.487 → ~0): causa raiz identificada na v4
  ============================================================================

  Diagnóstico definitivo após 3 iterações malsucedidas:

    A <img> LCP estava dentro de <modal-opener class="...no-js-hidden">.
    O tema carrega `base-v2.css` como preload async (stylesheet_tag: preload:
    true em layout/theme.liquid). Esse arquivo contém:

        html.no-js .no-js-hidden { display:none !important }

    O script que troca `no-js` → `js` no <html> fica na linha 183 do
    theme.liquid — depois de TODOS os preloads de CSS. Race condition:

    1. Parser emite <link rel="preload" as="style"> para base-v2.css. Browser
       começa a baixar em paralelo.
    2. Parser continua parseando <head>, emite critical CSS inline.
    3. base-v2.css termina de baixar e aplicar. Nesse momento, se o parser
       ainda não chegou na linha 183, `<html>` ainda tem class "no-js".
    4. A regra `html.no-js .no-js-hidden{display:none !important}` casa com
       o <modal-opener class="no-js-hidden"> e o esconde — junto com a
       <img> LCP e todo o wrapper de aspect-ratio que estava dentro dele.
    5. Parser chega na linha 183, script executa, troca a class para "js".
       Regra não casa mais, modal-opener reaparece.
    6. Entre os passos 4 e 5, o layout fica sem a imagem hero. Quando ela
       reaparece, todo o conteúdo abaixo é empurrado para baixo. CLS = altura
       total da imagem / viewport = ~0.49.

  Por que as v1/v2/v3 não resolveram:
    - Todas tentaram reservar espaço DENTRO do modal-opener (aspect-ratio no
      wrapper, width/height no img, DOM flat). Quando o pai vira display:none,
      os descendentes somem juntos — a reserva é inútil.

  Solução v4 (estrutura DOM nova para o caminho LCP):
    - <div.media-wrapper.product-media-wrapper--lcp>  ← wrapper externo, SEM
      classe no-js-hidden, com aspect-ratio inline. SEMPRE visível.
        <img class="product-media-img--lcp" width height src srcset ...>
           ← img como filha direta do wrapper, fora de qualquer custom
             element. Também sempre visível.
        {% if zoom %}
          <modal-opener class="product__modal-opener ..." data-modal="..."
                        style="position:absolute;inset:0;...">
             ← modal-opener agora é overlay absoluto SOBRE a img. Captura
               o clique para abrir o zoom modal. Não tem no-js-hidden — se
               JS está disabled, o overlay renderiza inerte (click sem
               efeito), a <img> abaixo permanece visível.
            <span.product__media-icon>[icon]</span>
            <button.product__media-toggle>[invisible clickable area]</button>
          </modal-opener>
        {% endif %}
      </div>

  Garantias:
    - A <img> nunca é afetada por `no-js-hidden` (pai direto é <div> sem class).
    - O wrapper reserva geometria via aspect-ratio inline + width:100% — zero
      dependência de CSS externo ou JS para resolver altura.
    - A <img> tem width/height explícitos como params do image_tag, o que
      faz o browser computar aspect-ratio nativo mesmo sem CSS.
    - Clique no overlay continua abrindo o modal normalmente (modal-opener
      custom element listens for descendant clicks).
    - Sem noscript fallback para o caminho LCP: a <img> real renderiza
      igualmente sem JS. Zoom não funciona sem JS, mas isso é o estado da
      arte em qualquer loja Shopify.

  Caminho não-LCP (slides 2+, videos, models, imagens lazy): mantém estrutura
  original com <use-animate> + <modal-opener>. Esses estão fora do viewport
  inicial e não causam CLS no primeiro paint.

  Recomendação adicional (fora deste snippet): mover o script
  `no-js`→`js` (layout/theme.liquid:183) para imediatamente após a abertura
  de <head>, antes de qualquer <link rel="preload" as="style">. Isso elimina
  o race condition globalmente e beneficia OUTROS elementos com no-js-hidden
  (slider buttons, price, footer blocks, etc.).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- if is_lcp_image -%}
  {%- comment -%} === LCP image path: flat DOM, <img> outside modal-opener === {%- endcomment -%}
  <div
    class="media-wrapper product-media-wrapper--lcp{% if settings.use_intrinsic_image_size_on_product_page %} media-wrapper--intrinsic-size{% endif %}"
    style="--intrinsic-width:{{ media.preview_image.width }}px;display:block;position:relative;overflow:hidden;width:100%;aspect-ratio:{{ preview_aspect }};"
  >
    {{ media.preview_image | image_url: width: 600 | image_tag:
      loading: 'eager',
      decoding: 'async',
      fetchpriority: 'high',
      sizes: sizes,
      widths: widths,
      width: media.preview_image.width,
      height: media.preview_image.height,
      alt: alt,
      class: 'product-media-img--lcp'
    }}

    {%- if zoom -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        Overlay absoluto: sem `no-js-hidden`. Se JS está disabled o
        overlay renderiza mas clique não faz nada — a <img> abaixo
        continua visível para o usuário.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <modal-opener
        class="product__modal-opener product__modal-opener--image product__modal-opener--lcp"
        data-modal="#ProductModal-{{ modal_id }}"
        style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:block;z-index:2;"
      >
        <span
          class="product__media-icon motion-reduce"
          aria-hidden="true"
          style="position:absolute;top:1rem;right:1rem;z-index:3;pointer-events:none;"
        >
          {%- render 'icon', icon: 'zoom' -%}
        </span>
        <button
          class="product__media-toggle product__media-toggle--lcp"
          type="button"
          aria-haspopup="dialog"
          data-media-id="{{ media.id }}"
          style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;background:transparent;border:0;padding:0;margin:0;cursor:zoom-in;"
        >
          <span class="visually-hidden">
            {{- 'products.product.media.open_media' | t -}}
          </span>
        </button>
      </modal-opener>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

{%- else -%}
  {%- comment -%} === Non-LCP path: mantém estrutura original === {%- endcomment -%}

  <noscript>
    {%- if media.media_type == 'video' or media.media_type == 'external_video' -%}
      <a href="{% if media.media_type == 'video' %}{{ media.sources[1].url }}{% else %}{{ media | external_video_url }}{% endif %}" aria-label="{{ 'products.product.video_exit_message' | t: title: product.title | escape }}">
        {%- if zoom -%}
          <span class="product__media-icon motion-reduce">
            {% render 'icon', icon: 'play' %}
          </span>
        {%- endif -%}
        <div class="media-wrapper">
          <div class="product__media media media--{{ image_ratio }}{% if mobile_image_ratio %} media-mobile--{{ mobile_image_ratio }}{% endif %}"
            {%- if image_ratio == 'adapt' or mobile_image_ratio == 'adapt' %} style="--image-ratio-percent: {{ 1 | divided_by: media.preview_image.aspect_ratio | times: 100 }}%;"{% endif -%}
          >
            {{ media.preview_image | image_url: width: 1200 | image_tag:
              loading: image_loading,
              decoding: image_decoding,
              fetchpriority: image_fetchpriority,
              sizes: sizes,
              widths: widths,
              width: media.preview_image.width,
              height: media.preview_image.height,
              alt: alt
            }}
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
    {%- else -%}
      <div class="media-wrapper">
        <div class="product__media media media--{{ image_ratio }}{% if mobile_image_ratio %} media-mobile--{{ mobile_image_ratio }}{% endif %}"
          {%- if image_ratio == 'adapt' or mobile_image_ratio == 'adapt' %} style="--image-ratio-percent: {{ 1 | divided_by: media.preview_image.aspect_ratio | times: 100 }}%;"{% endif -%}
        >
          {{ media.preview_image | image_url: width: 1200 | image_tag:
            loading: image_loading,
            decoding: image_decoding,
            fetchpriority: image_fetchpriority,
            sizes: sizes,
            widths: widths,
            width: media.preview_image.width,
            height: media.preview_image.height,
            alt: alt,
            is: 'lazy-image'
          }}
        </div>
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </noscript>

  <modal-opener class="product__modal-opener product__modal-opener--{{ media.media_type }} no-js-hidden" data-modal="#ProductModal-{{ modal_id }}">
    {%- if zoom -%}
      <span class="product__media-icon motion-reduce" aria-hidden="true">
        {%- liquid
          case media.media_type
          when 'video' or 'external_video'
            render 'icon', icon: 'play'
          when 'model'
            render 'icon', icon: '3d-model'
          else
            render 'icon', icon: 'zoom'
          endcase
        -%}
      </span>
    {%- endif -%}

    <use-animate data-animate="{% if position == 'featured' %}zoom-fade-small{% else %}fade-up{% endif %}" style="--intrinsic-width:{{ media.preview_image.width }}px;aspect-ratio:{{ preview_aspect }};" class="media-wrapper{% if settings.use_intrinsic_image_size_on_product_page %} media-wrapper--intrinsic-size{% endif %}">
      <div class="product__media image-animate media media--{{ image_ratio }}{% if mobile_image_ratio %} media-mobile--{{ mobile_image_ratio }}{% endif %}"
        {%- if image_ratio == 'adapt' or mobile_image_ratio == 'adapt' %} style="--image-ratio-percent: {{ 1 | divided_by: preview_aspect | times: 100 }}%;"{% endif -%}
      >
        {{ media.preview_image | image_url: width: 1200 | image_tag:
          loading: image_loading,
          decoding: image_decoding,
          fetchpriority: image_fetchpriority,
          sizes: sizes,
          widths: widths,
          width: media.preview_image.width,
          height: media.preview_image.height,
          alt: alt,
          is: 'lazy-image'
        }}
      </div>
    </use-animate>

    {%- if zoom -%}
      <button class="product__media-toggle" type="button" aria-haspopup="dialog" data-media-id="{{ media.id }}">
        <span class="visually-hidden">
          {%- if position == 'featured' %}
            {{ 'products.product.media.open_media' | t }}
          {%- else -%}
            {{ 'products.product.media.open_media' | t: index: position }}
          {%- endif -%}
        </span>
      </button>
    {%- endif -%}
  </modal-opener>

{%- endif -%}

{%- if media.media_type != 'image' -%}
  <div class="media-wrapper">
    {%- if media.media_type == 'model' -%}
      <product-model class="deferred-media media media--{{ image_ratio }}{% if mobile_image_ratio %} media-mobile--{{ mobile_image_ratio }}{% endif %} no-js-hidden"
        data-media-id="{{ media.id }}"
        {%- if image_ratio == 'adapt' or mobile_image_ratio == 'adapt' %} style="--image-ratio-percent: 100%;"{% endif -%}
      >
    {%- else -%}
      <deferred-media class="deferred-media media media--{{ image_ratio }}{% if mobile_image_ratio %} media-mobile--{{ mobile_image_ratio }}{% endif %} no-js-hidden"
        data-media-id="{{ media.id }}"
        {%- if image_ratio == 'adapt' or mobile_image_ratio == 'adapt' %} style="--image-ratio-percent: {{ 1 | divided_by: media.aspect_ratio | times: 100 }}%;"{% endif -%}
      >
    {%- endif -%}
    {{ media.preview_image | image_url: width: 1200 | image_tag:
      loading: image_loading,
      decoding: image_decoding,
      fetchpriority: image_fetchpriority,
      class: 'deferred-media__poster',
      sizes: sizes,
      widths: widths,
      width: media.preview_image.width,
      height: media.preview_image.height,
      alt: alt
    }}
    <button id="Deferred-Poster-{{ media.id }}" class="deferred-media__poster" type="button">
      <span class="deferred-media__poster-button motion-reduce">
        {%- if media.media_type == 'model' -%}
          <span class="visually-hidden">{{ 'products.product.media.play_model' | t }}</span>
          {%- render 'icon', icon: '3d-model' -%}
        {%- else -%}
          <span class="visually-hidden">{{ 'products.product.media.play_video' | t }}</span>
          {%- render 'icon', icon: 'play' -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      </span>
    </button>
    <template>
      {%- liquid
        case media.media_type
        when 'external_video'
          assign video_class = 'js-' | append: media.host
          if media.host == 'youtube'
            echo media | external_video_url: autoplay: true, loop: loop, playlist: media.external_id | external_video_tag: class: video_class, loading: "lazy"
          else
            echo media | external_video_url: autoplay: true, loop: loop | external_video_tag: class: video_class, loading: "lazy"
          endif
        when 'video'
          echo media | media_tag: image_size: "2048x", autoplay: true, loop: loop, controls: true, controlsList: "nodownload", preload: "none"
        when 'model'
          echo media | media_tag: image_size: "2048x", toggleable: true
        endcase
      -%}
    </template>

    {%- if media.media_type == 'model' -%}
      </product-model>
      {%- if xr_button -%}
        <button
          class="button button--full-width product__xr-button"
          type="button"
          aria-label="{{ 'products.product.xr_button_label' | t }}"
          data-shopify-xr
          data-shopify-model3d-id="{{ media.id }}"
          data-shopify-title="title"
          data-shopify-xr-hidden
        >
          {% render 'icon', icon: '3d-model' %}
          {{ 'products.product.xr_button' | t }}
        </button>
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- else -%}
      </deferred-media>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
